snippet.textDisplay: This literally happened to me, I am naturally dark blonde and bleached it with box dye (BIG MISTAKE) some parts were white and the top was orange and yellow, being 13 and caring about the way I look to other people I cried and got so upset I started to be sick, (I wore a beenie for a week, including Christmas Day)after reading the box and I knew I should have left it 2 weeks but decided to dye it back to a color more like my natural hair before that. Not even a week after that I got it done professionally and got it lightened with a professional softer bleach and now I absolutely love it. Somehow my hair is not in terrible condition and is fine , even though I bleached it 3 times in 2 week. If you are thinking about doing this yourself, please do not, it is not smart  and it might go wrong

snippet.textDisplay: I have a similar colour to this girl's hair naturally and I was ombre for a while and then bleached the ombred hair about a year later after ombreing every 4 months or so and I went pretty blonde and was lucky it didn't get destroyed. I then went pink and blue for 1 year and a half after then bleached it again. My hair was wrecked, Luckily I decided to get my hair cut shoulder length so there was some blonde left but all the dead ends were gone. I THEN proceeded to go from pink, orange, brown and peach over the course of a year and then decided to bleach my hair again. Lets just say it didn't turn out the platinum blonde it was after the pink and blue. 3 weeks later I shaved my head. I had always wanted to do it so I killed two birds with one stone and shaved it for charity so I wasn't a complete Britney moment. Now my hair is back to my shoulders nearly 1 years on and I will say I have thoughts of going back to the ombre HOWEVER. After reading this story I hope anyone with very dark brown hair treats their hair with the respect it deserves ahaha! I'll never get back to this point, just pay the money for someone to do it for you! It'll be worth it!

snippet.textDisplay: Ummm yeah at 16:56 I'm not understanding exactly what there is to laugh and giggle about when you're friends hair is actually falling out...she has already lost the same amount and a toddler has at their 1st trim haircut. When you have absolutely no idea no knowledge no training in hair styling/colouring you shouldn't have done it to begin with. If you didn't go to a professional and tried it yourself at home you should have stopped immediately after the 1st attempt didn't work and then seek professional help immediately...but no they did it 2 more times with chemicals that they have no knowledge or understanding of how they interact with the human hair and it's many different shades. As bad as I'm going to feel for this young girl when she is literally bald after starting with gorgeous hair, I'm also going to say good lesson hopefully learned and she never tries again for herself but goes to a professional!

snippet.textDisplay: Idk why is everyone only blaming her friends and saying it's their fault as if she was a victim. She literally asked her friends who had zero clue what they were doing to continuously bleach her hair over and over again thinking that somehow after so many fails it would miraculously get better. Did ANY of them even bother researching? Clearly not, and if she wants to go blonde at home it's her responsibility to do so, or handle the consequences. Her friends didn't force her to bleach her hair, she herself chose to do it and for some reason asked her friends do it over and over instead of going to someone competent. Her friends should have known when to stop, but she should have known better than bleaching multiple times with people that don't know how to do hair. She honestly didn't seem to care at all about what happened to her hair.
